set current user "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
================================================================

NAME
----

set current user - This function can be replaced via

SYNOPSIS
--------

This function can be replaced via
[plugins](/Glossary#plugins "Glossary"). If plugins do not redefine
these functions, then this will be used instead.

Changes the current user by ID or name.

Set `$id` to null and specify a name if you do not know a user's ID.

USAGE
-----

` <?php set_current_user( $id, $name ) ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$id` 
:   ([*integer|null*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer.7Cnull "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) User ID.
    Default: *None*

 `$name` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) The user's username
    Default: ''

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `(object)` 
:   returns values returned by
    [`wp_set_current_user()`](/Function_Reference/wp_set_current_user "Function Reference/wp set current user")

EXAMPLES
--------

NOTES
-----

-   This function can be replaced via
    [plugins](/Glossary#plugins "Glossary"). If plugins do not redefine
    these functions, then this will be used instead.
-   Uses:
    [`wp_set_current_user()`](/Function_Reference/wp_set_current_user "Function Reference/wp set current user")

CHANGE LOG
----------

